# HTML / Jinja2 Review: Structure, Security & Design System

You are working in a **multi-tenant SaaS** using Flask, Jinja2, vanilla JS, and HTMX. The SPA shell is `app/core/frontend/shared/base_spa.html`. Shared partials/macros live in `app/core/frontend/shared/`. Before finalising any HTML template you write or modify, check every rule below and fix violations inline.

---

## STRUCTURE

### 1. Extend `base_spa.html` — Never Write Standalone HTML Pages

`base_spa.html` provides the shell, sidebar, CSRF meta tag, global CSS, font loading, theme init, and the `#page-content` HTMX swap target. Bypassing it silently breaks multiple things.

**BAD**:
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/static/styles.css">
  <meta name="csrf-token" content="{{ csrf_token() }}">
</head>
<body>
  <!-- reimplementing sidebar... -->
```
**GOOD**:
```html
{% extends "shared/base_spa.html" %}
{% block title %}Inventory{% endblock %}
{% block head_extras %}
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="{{ url_for('core.serve_core_css', filename='inventory-spa-header.css') }}">
{% endblock %}
{% block content %}
  <div id="page-content" class="page-content">...</div>
{% endblock %}
```

---

### 2. Use Shared Partials and Macros — Never Duplicate Their Markup

| Need | What to use |
|---|---|
| Page title + subtitle + optional CTA | `{% from 'shared/page_header.html' import page_header %}` → `{{ page_header(title, subtitle, href, label) }}` |
| Content card with heading | `{% from 'shared/primary_card.html' import primary_card %}` → `{% call primary_card(title) %}…{% endcall %}` |
| Sidebar | Already in `base_spa.html` — never include manually |
| Delete confirmation modal | `{% include 'shared/delete-doc-confirm-modal.html' %}` |
| Execution modal | `{% include 'shared/execution-modal.html' %}` |
| Sticky bottom action bar | Set `spa_fixed_action_right_html`, then `{% include 'shared/spa-fixed-action-bar.html' %}` |
| Back link | `{% include 'shared/back_link.html' %}` |

**BAD** — hand-rolling a page header:
```html
<div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center;">
  <h1 style="font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 600;">Inventory</h1>
  <a href="/inventory/add" class="btn btn-primary">Add Item</a>
</div>
```
**GOOD**:
```html
{% from 'shared/page_header.html' import page_header %}
{{ page_header(title="Inventory", primary_action_href="/inventory/add", primary_action_label="Add Item") }}
```

---

## SECURITY

### 3. Never Use `| safe` on User-Supplied Values — XSS

Jinja2 autoescapes `{{ var }}` by default. `| safe` disables that.

**BAD**: `<h2>{{ user.name | safe }}</h2>` — XSS if user.name contains `<script>`.
**GOOD**: `<h2>{{ user.name }}</h2>` — autoescaped, no change needed.

`| safe` is only acceptable for known-safe, developer-controlled HTML (e.g. a hardcoded SVG string built in Python).

---

### 4. Don't Put Sensitive Data in `data-*` Attributes or Hidden Inputs

`data-*` and `<input type="hidden">` are fully visible in devtools. Never put session tokens, API keys, or org secrets there.

**BAD**:
```html
<div data-user-token="{{ session_token }}" data-org-secret="{{ org_api_key }}">
<input type="hidden" name="org_id" value="{{ current_org_id }}">
```
**GOOD**: The backend reads `g.current_org_id` from the session — it never trusts a client-submitted `org_id`. UI correlation IDs (non-privileged) are fine in `data-*`.

---

### 5. Feature-Gated Pages Must Be Gated Server-Side

Template conditionals are cosmetic — direct requests bypass them.

**BAD**: `{% if current_user.org.crm_enabled %}<a href="/crm">CRM</a>{% endif %}` while `/crm` routes are always registered.
**GOOD**: `crm_bp` is only registered in the app factory when `crm_enabled` is `True`. The template link is a UX hint, not the gate.

---

## DESIGN SYSTEM

### 6. Use CSS Variables and Design-System Classes — No Hardcoded Colours

**BAD**: `<button style="background: #3b82f6; color: white; border-radius: 8px;">Save</button>`
**GOOD**: `<button class="btn btn-primary">Save</button>`

Key tokens: `var(--primary)`, `var(--text-primary)`, `var(--text-secondary)`, `var(--text-tertiary)`, `var(--bg-card)`, `var(--bg-app)`, `var(--border-default)`, `var(--error)`, `var(--success)`, `var(--radius-md/lg/xl)`, `var(--shadow-lg)`.

Utility classes: `btn btn-primary`, `btn btn-secondary`, `btn btn-glass`, `card`, `glass-card`, `page-title`, `page-subtitle`, `card-title`, `card-content`.

---

### 7. Scope Page-Specific CSS — Don't Add Unscoped Rules Globally

Unscoped rules in `styles2.css` or `base_spa.html` affect every page.

**BAD** in a global stylesheet: `.table-row { background: var(--bg-card); }`
**GOOD** in `{% block head_extras %}`:
```html
{% block head_extras %}
<style>
  .inventory-view .table-row { background: var(--bg-card); }
</style>
{% endblock %}
```

---

## HTMX

### 8. Always Swap Into `#page-content`

**BAD**: `<a hx-get="/inventory" hx-target="#main">Inventory</a>` — wrong target breaks sidebar and scroll.
**GOOD**: `<a hx-get="/inventory" hx-target="#page-content" hx-swap="innerHTML">Inventory</a>`

For intentional full-page navigation across blueprints: `<a href="/core" hx-boost="false">Core</a>`

---

## ACCESSIBILITY

### 9. Labels, Roles, and `aria-*` on Interactive Elements

**BAD**:
```html
<input type="text" placeholder="Search...">
<button onclick="deleteItem(id)"><svg>…</svg></button>
```
**GOOD**:
```html
<label for="search-input">Search</label>
<input id="search-input" type="text" placeholder="Search…">
<button onclick="deleteItem(id)" aria-label="Delete item"><svg aria-hidden="true">…</svg></button>
```

Modals need `role="dialog" aria-modal="true" aria-labelledby="<heading-id>"`.

---

## CHECKLIST

- [ ] Page extends `shared/base_spa.html` — no standalone `<!DOCTYPE html>`
- [ ] Shared partials/macros used instead of hand-rolled markup
- [ ] No `| safe` on user-supplied Jinja2 values
- [ ] No sensitive data in `data-*` attributes or `<input type="hidden">`
- [ ] Feature gates enforced server-side (blueprint registration), not only in templates
- [ ] No hardcoded hex colours — CSS variables and design-system classes used
- [ ] Page-specific CSS scoped to a component class, not added globally
- [ ] HTMX swaps target `#page-content`; cross-blueprint links use `hx-boost="false"`
- [ ] Every `<input>` has an associated `<label>`; icon buttons have `aria-label`
